<paragraph blockId="7.[813,1457,1183,1340]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">
NOTES. — Can be a problem on yam cuttings during conservation and before planting. 
<bibRefCitation author="COHIC F." box="[1075,1223,1210,1234]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136" refId="ref28090" refString="COHIC F. 1958 a. - Contribution a l'etude des cochenilles d'interet economique de Nouvelle-Caledonie et Dependances. South Pacific Commission, Technical Paper 116: 35 p." type="book" year="1958">Cohic (1958a)</bibRefCitation>
noted that it was only known from the Isle of Pines and 
<collectingRegion box="[1155,1306,1236,1260]" country="New Caledonia" name="Province des Iles" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Loyalty Islands</collectingRegion>
, but today it is widespread within the whole archipelago, most likely due to numerous exchanges of yam cuttings for planting and during traditional customary ceremonies.
</paragraph>
